simplesect.para:
pCoeffs points to the array of filter coefficients stored in time reversed order: 
   {b[numTaps-1], b[numTaps-2], b[N-2], ..., b[1], b[0]}
 The initial filter coefficients serve as a starting point for the adaptive filter. pState points to an array of length numTaps+blockSize-1 samples, where blockSize is the number of input samples processed by each call to riscv_lms_norm_f32().

pCoeffs points to the array of filter coefficients stored in time reversed order: 
   {b[numTaps-1], b[numTaps-2], b[N-2], ..., b[1], b[0]}
 The initial filter coefficients serve as a starting point for the adaptive filter. pState points to the array of state variables and size of array is numTaps+blockSize-1 samples, where blockSize is the number of input samples processed by each call to riscv_lms_norm_q15().

pCoeffs points to the array of filter coefficients stored in time reversed order: 
   {b[numTaps-1], b[numTaps-2], b[N-2], ..., b[1], b[0]}
 The initial filter coefficients serve as a starting point for the adaptive filter. pState points to an array of length numTaps+blockSize-1 samples, where blockSize is the number of input samples processed by each call to riscv_lms_norm_q31().
